		{
			dependencies: ["708D8EA7F48BBCC9"]
			description: [
				"Basic method of rotational energy generation. Water wheels generate energy when placed above flowing water. If the water is still, the wheel will not spin."
				""
				"&e-&r There are two sizes: small and large. Small ones generate 256 &9SU&r at &932 RPM&r and large ones generate 512 &9SU&r at &916 RPM&r"
				""
				"&c⚠ Alert &r: Water wheels used to generate more energy based on the amount of flowing water in contact, but this feature has been removed."
			]
			id: "719CCBB870F4E1BB"
			rewards: [{
